comments.body:
Thanks for reaching out, @zephyros-dev !

I am open to allow for tweaking the `kube down` command.  I guess a `KubeDownForce=true` field would do the trick as well.

@ygalblum WDYT?

@zephyros-dev I agree about UX parts of your comment. Obviously handing a single service is preferable. But, I was focusing on what is available since I do not know of a way to differentiate between restart and stop. According to @vrothberg there are ways to do that, and if so, that's great.

Having said that, I do want to emphasis that I did not talk about `.volume` units, but instead of **one** additional `.kube` unit file. My suggestion is to take all PVCs (one or more) from the original YAML file and place them under a new K8S YAML file. Then have two `.kube` units, one for the volume(s) and the other for the application.

As I wrote, currently, `.kube` based units generate an error if the YAML file does not contain any containers (due to the need to change the Type to `oneshot`). Now, since `KubeDownForce` is not supported yet either, the current version does not fulfill the requirement anyhow. However, these fixes are fairly simple and we could support the less-UX-friendly option with a minimal effort.
